✅ Real Fix (What you must do)

✔️ 1. Embed mirror config into ISO (CRITICAL)

When creating agent ISO, you MUST include:

openshift-install agent create image \
  --dir <install-dir>

👉 This uses install-config.yaml


---

✔️ 2. Ensure install-config.yaml uses mirror (NOT deprecated field)

You are using:

imageContentSources:

❌ Deprecated → may be ignored partially

👉 Replace with:

imageDigestSources:
- mirrors:
  - mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4/openshift/release-images
  source: quay.io/openshift-release-dev/ocp-release
- mirrors:
  - mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4/openshift/release
  source: quay.io/openshift-release-dev/ocp-v4.0-art-dev


---

✔️ 3. VERY IMPORTANT → Set releaseImage explicitly

This avoids quay.io lookup completely:

Add in install-config.yaml:

releaseImage: mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4:4.19.23-x86_64

👉 This is the most important fix 🔥


---

✔️ 4. Verify mirror registry is reachable from node

From agent shell (Ctrl+Alt+F2):

curl -k https://mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan:8443/v2/

If this fails → installer falls back to quay.io ❌


---

✔️ 5. Disable IPv6 (highly recommended in your case)

Your error clearly shows IPv6 DNS failure.

👉 Update ALL hosts in agent-config.yaml:

ipv6:
  enabled: false


---

✔️ 6. DNS should resolve ONLY internal

Test:

dig mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan

👉 If DNS fails → installer tries internet → FAIL


